4
00:00:13,640 --> 00:00:15,260
So what is minimal APIs?

5
00:00:15,290 --> 00:00:23,060
Minimal APIs provide a simplified approach for building fast and efficient Http APIs in ASP.Net core.

6
00:00:23,690 --> 00:00:30,680
They enable you to create fully functional Rest endpoints with minimal coding and configuration, reducing

7
00:00:30,680 --> 00:00:34,910
the need for the traditional scaffolding and unnecessary controllers.

8
00:00:35,390 --> 00:00:42,710
We can skip the traditional scaffolding and avoid the unnecessary controllers by fluent decorating API

9
00:00:42,710 --> 00:00:44,270
routes and actions.

10
00:00:45,050 --> 00:00:47,480
Here you can see the basic example.

11
00:00:47,480 --> 00:00:54,230
Basically, we will use top level statement and in the first row we will creating a web application

12
00:00:54,230 --> 00:00:58,610
and mapping the Http get request to the root path.

13
00:00:58,610 --> 00:01:00,950
And it is basically simplified.

14
00:01:00,950 --> 00:01:04,610
Return the hello world for every request.

15
00:01:04,700 --> 00:01:12,140
So this shows the easy of setting up a basic http api endpoint with minimal APIs.

16
00:01:13,560 --> 00:01:17,580
Minimal APIs also supporting dynamic routing.

17
00:01:17,580 --> 00:01:20,490
You can see example code in here.

18
00:01:20,700 --> 00:01:27,960
This time we will have a route parameters for using the user ID and book ID.

19
00:01:28,110 --> 00:01:32,310
In this example we will also exposing Http get request.

20
00:01:32,310 --> 00:01:40,980
But this route has some dynamic routing parameters which are the user ID and book ID and the API business

21
00:01:40,980 --> 00:01:48,360
internal code basically respond with these IDs and basic text with including the user ID and book ID

22
00:01:48,360 --> 00:01:49,350
is in here.

23
00:01:49,350 --> 00:01:57,210
So in this demonstration, we can show that how easily you can handle more complex routing scenarios

24
